<title>Gain over PCM</title>
<metadata>
  <md:content-id>m32146</md:content-id><md:title>Gain over PCM</md:title>
  <md:abstract>The total reconstruction error of transform coding with optimal bit allocation is compared to that of uniformly quantized PCM, and the ratio is found to depend on a type of spectral flatness measure.</md:abstract>
  <md:uuid>e65b3c09-6cdc-499d-a5fe-2402563cf063</md:uuid>
</metadata>

<content>
 




        <list id="id205671" display="block" list-type="bulleted"><item id="uid18">With an orthogonal transform and the optimal bit allocation
<link document="m32123" target-id="uid11">equation 8 from Optimal Bit Allocation</link> (lower equation), the total reconstruction error equals
<equation id="uid19"><m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display"><m:msubsup><m:mi>σ</m:mi><m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msubsup><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mo>|</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mi>T</m:mi><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mspace width="3.33333pt"/><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mspace width="3.33333pt"/><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mi>N</m:mi></m:mfrac><m:munderover><m:mrow><m:mo>∑</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>ℓ</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>N</m:mi><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:munderover><m:msubsup><m:mi>σ</m:mi><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>q</m:mi><m:mi>ℓ</m:mi></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msubsup><m:mspace width="3.33333pt"/><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mspace width="3.33333pt"/><m:msub><m:mi>γ</m:mi><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:msub><m:msup><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mrow><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>R</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msup><m:msup><m:mfenced separators="" open="(" close=")"><m:munderover><m:mrow><m:mo>∏</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>k</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>N</m:mi><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:munderover><m:msubsup><m:mi>σ</m:mi><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mi>k</m:mi></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msubsup></m:mfenced><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>/</m:mo><m:mi>N</m:mi></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></equation>
